<subSubSection id="35DD6735AFAA13E971BD502A77F63F4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="29E1C90FF05221D4D23A27E5D0E1C569" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CEA1EE6A22F5D21DB62C02A24EDEB9DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName id="7E16D864173CF7B9C0A7980FD3BABF4D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Lomelosia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lomelosia rhodopensis" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhodopensis">
<emphasis id="1D741A5C529700E617D31E8B330DC779" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Lomelosia rhodopensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare, range-restricted species endemic to NE Greece and south Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="862A0EA3568C52729978355ED2F3AB78" author="Kokkini, S." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668846" refString="Kokkini, S., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Kokkini 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Greek specimens had been collected only from Mt. Falakro (
<bibRefCitation id="0739740D7D5226E85B2826A3AB1C33C6" author="Kokkini, S." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668846" refString="Kokkini, S., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Kokkini 1991</bibRefCitation>
), while an observation from Nomos Serron (
<bibRefCitation id="54E9F54883073B47D1D7774C7D715BC9" author="Tan, K." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 26 (3): 537 - 572" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670041" refString="Tan, K., Kofinas, G., 2020. New floristic records in the Balkans: 43. Phytologia Balcanica, 26 (3): 537-572" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 43" year="2020">Tan and Kofinas 2020</bibRefCitation>
) added a second locality. This is the third confirmed population found in the Greek territory (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="129C927CB43510ECFA392111513EAB5F" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F7677669" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution map of Convolvulus suendermannii, Lomelosia rhodopensis, Drymocallis rupestris and Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656581" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
